Detection of different types of image editing operations carried out on an image is an important problem in image forensics.
It gives information about images, and also can show fake images.
There have been a few methods proposed to detect different types of image editing operations in a single framework.
However, all operations have to be known from the start of training phase.
In forensic cases it may not be possible to know about the editing operations carried out on an image.
we propose a new tool which can tell the difference between edited images
The proposed method classifies image patches in a pair by pair as either similarly or differently processed using a deep siamese neural network.
Once the network learns to distinguish between different image editing operations, it can distinguish between different image editing operations not present in the training stage.
The experimental results show the efficacy of the proposed method in detecting/discriminating different image editing operations.
