A pharmacophore analysis was used to investigate and compare various types of compounds relevant to the drug discovery process (specifically, drug molecules, chemical building blocks and nondrug molecules).
Significant differences were observed between the drug properties and those obtained for the screening compounds, which appear to be closely related to non-drug properties.
It is suggested that the analysis of pharmacophore profiles could be used as an additional tool for selecting compounds based on properties for library design, thus improving the odds of success in lead discovery projects.
